I Can't explain the feeling I had this weekend visiting ST. Jude, I met this robust and sweet-spirited kid Emmanuel and his beautiful mother. Emmanuel was diagnosed with cancer as a very young child and eventually had to get a prostatic eye, but that didn't stop Emmanuel's dreams of playing football. He ended up receiving 27 scholarships to play football, and he is now cancer free! I loved our time together painting and sharing in the spirit of perseverance. I asked God to lead me to a more purposeful life, and he sent me on a plane ride to Memphis, where not only I got a chance to meet some wonderful, inspiring kids but also got a chance to learn so much about a city that is so rich in black history! My heart is left whole, and my journey to live more purposefully is just starting.

@tttorrez from our sister station, @hot97 at the @nationalactionnetwork talking about the impact of hip hop. 💎

“Hip hop saved a lot of our lives” 🎤

Female Hip Hop artists have been dominating the airwaves, but their voices are often drowned out by men who create the narratives, and I hope to be a voice to represent all women in the culture, from the executive to the talent side. I’m so excited about this new show and to look at where I first started at Hot in 2014, returning to school, earning my business degree during the pandemic, and working hard to achieve this promotion; I’m fulfilling my dream of representing women of color in the workplace, my most crucial role is to elevate and open doors for the women coming up! 

Also, I get to work every day on air with one of my idols @DJEnuff, who is the most amazing human being! I also work on air with the amazing @sodrewski, who has deep connections with this generation of artists and music lovers! I couldn’t ask for a better team! Thank you to my fantastic @hot97 team! Thank you to @pioferro for always teaching and pushing me to levels! I’m so humbled and grateful to return to the airwaves every day!

PRESS Release: 
In addition to her programming duties HOT 97’s Vice President, Music Director and Multimedia Personality TT Torrez will lead the new radio show Tap in With TT, which brings new energy and fresh content from start to finish. At noon, 25-year HOT 97 vet and hip hop legend DJ Enuff will deliver his signature style to the lunch-time crowd with “It’s Enuff Midday Mix,” an hour-long mix featuring the biggest hits in the culture. DJ Drewski, known for his deep connection with this generation of music lovers and artists, will close out the show with the “New at 2 with Drewski,” a segment spotlighting the newest and most exciting emerging Hip Hop artists.

As Hip-Hop and music culture evolves, Tap in With TT will be a full interactive content show that will leave the audience wanting more. “I’m fulfilling my dream as a voice of women in the culture, from the business side to on-air, which is especially poignant at a time when female hip hop artists have dominated the airwaves. As I move to the midday host, I will be sure to expand my role as a mentor and elevate other women in the industry.” says TT Torrez, Vice President, Music Director and Muti-Media Personality at Hot 97.
 
 Torrez’s ongoing support for women is reflected in the 2023 HOT 97 Summer Jam lineup, which features headliner Cardi B along with rising female artists including Ice Spice, Lola Brooke, Coi Leray and GloRilla. The iconic Hip-Hop music festival returns to New York June 4th at the new UBS Arena at Belmont Park, in Elmont, NY.

“We are thrilled to bring a vibrant new crew to daytime with Tap in With TT. TT Torrez, DJ Drewski, and DJ Enuff bring a fresh dynamic and diverse perspectives that showcase the evolution of hip hop and the spirit of HOT 97,” says Rahsan-Rahsan Lindsay, CEO of MediaCo.

Hot 97’s Senior VP of Programming, Pio Ferro, called Torrez “One of our industry’s most respected execs and talents with an incredible work ethic. TT, Enuff, and Drewski bring tremendous experience and talent to the airwaves, and we expect that same experience, skill, and energy during middays.”

Last night I had the best bonding time with my son at the @champagnepapi concert. I was happy and sad at the same time! Happy because I got to take him to his first concert to see one of his favorite artists! Sad because he is growing up so fast!!!

I remember when he was in my belly, one of my colleagues used to say to me all the time, YOU have more adult years than you do kid years, so cherish everything and every moment because it will go by fast, and man, this is so true!!! 

So take time and create as many happy memories with your kids that will last a lifetime!!!! I love you, SON, and I’m glad I got to share this moment with you! ❤️

TT Torrez Presents Dreams And Beyond Young Women's Empowerment Dinner ❤️ 🎁🙏🏾
All the starts from the BRONX came to support these young women and there future  last week I saw the Dedication and the passion that some industry women and Artist/ Actresses have in supporting young teens Roads & Journeys in this Cold world I pray may you continue your success

Back in January, God put it in my heart to do more than what I was doing. I love being on the radio, and I love being an executive. As I grow and evolve, my spirit calls me to serve and lead the next generation behind me. That desire led me to launch my foundation, focusing on women’s empowerment and leadership for black and brown girls from under-resourced communities. On Nov 21, I teamed up with @bronxworks to launch my first event, a pre-Thanksgiving dinner for 20 amazing girls from the Bronx. Words can’t describe how beautiful the night was. 

The young women were offered various dress style options generously provided by the cure violence organization @streetcornerres @edwingdangeloofficial! To perfect their looks on the dinner day, the girls received glam makeovers by @KayMakeup  and @julianVega! 

Thank you to  @_conniediiamond and  @annaliseazadian for your electrifying performances! Thank You, @DreamDoll, for inspiring the girls with words on dreaming significance no matter the circumstances– the sky’s the limit. Thank you  @latto777 @bia @lola.brooke  @pinkpantheress @imbabytate @rapsody for your video of encouraging words! Thank you @djladys and @djneeshblack for keeping the vibes going! 

Thank you to my entire team @roseaym from the Now PR agency for making sure everything was buttoned up from top to bottom; thank you, Mimi, from @nevaehleheventsandweddings for the beautiful decor, and thank you @beatsronyc for hosting our event and for providing that amazing soul food spread! Everything was excellent! My heart is whole, and more work is to be done! Love to everyone!

Last but not least, I want to send love and all the positive energy the universe offers to all the fantastic young ladies in attendance. Your future is so bright, with endless possibilities! I pray you walked away feeling more potent than when you came in! ❤️❤️

Thank you to my production team for capturing the night @foto.don & @joedajour and the legendary @johnnynunez
A night to remember 🖤 Thank you beautiful queens for allowing me the opportunity to be in your presence🖤
All the girls looked so beautiful 🖤
